ThinkGlobal

We push our boundless ambition to integrate ourselves with global communities. In the process, we’ve successfully supported a diverse and multinational workforce, and have sealed a growing presence in multiple geographies. Our presence across various geographies of the world enables us to help global communities Rise.

    GlobalACQUISITIONS

    1947

    Beginning our journey with the Willys Jeep

    Our humble beginnings never stopped us from dreaming big. The brainchild of the Mahindra brothers and Ghulam Mohammed, M&M was born in 1945 in Mumbai as a steel trading company. Our alliance with the US started with a franchise to assemble the iconic WWII Willys Jeep, perfect for India’s rugged terrain.
    1954

    Manufacturing the Willys Jeep

    We entered into a technical and financial collaboration with Willys Overland Corporation, for the manufacture of the Jeep in India. Now, almost 70 years later, we are India’s premier utility vehicle company with a presence across 70 countries in six continents.
    1955

    Being listed a year later

    We went public in June 1955, within a year since we started manufacturing the Willys in India. Our shares were listed on the Bombay Stock Exchange in 1956. Today, we feature among the world’s largest and most powerful public companies.
    1961

    Venturing into farm equipment

    Mahindra’s farm equipment sector began as a joint venture in 1963 with the International Harvester Company of Chicago, USA. It gave a fillip to India’s green revolution, initiating the mechanisation of Indian agriculture.
    1993

    Building a world-class organization

    Our debut in the world financial market was marked by a maiden GDR issue of US $75 million. In 1994, we underwent reorganisation into six strategic business units: Automotive, Farm Equipment, Infrastructure, Trade and Financial Services, IT and Automotive Components.
    1994

    MUSA is born

    Our farm-equipment division, MUSA began its journey at Tomball, Texas, for the distribution of tractors. A favourite with small hobby farmers and landowners in North America, our tractors have hit #3 on market share. With 5 assembly centers and 530 dealerships, we have sold 140,000 tractors in North America.
    1996

    Mahindra partners with Ford

    Mahindra Ford India Ltd. was a joint venture with Ford Motor Co., USA, to manufacture two popular Ford passenger cars for the Indian market – Escort and Fiesta. Later on, we went on to manufacture the Scorpio, our best-selling SUV, built for the global market.
    2003

    The winning year for MUSA

    MUSA achieved the feat of being the first tractor company in the world to win the prestigious Deming Application Prize in 2003 and the Japan Quality Medal for customer focus in 2007. It was later merged with our parent company.
    2004

    Supply chain through Bristlecone Inc.

    We acquired Bristlecone Inc., California, a supply chain IT solutions company. It then helped us prepare our companies for new age platforms like the Internet of Things and also advised us on the technology needed to strengthen our supply chains. This venture has eventually helped us achieve a Gartner Top 10 rating.
    2009

    Mahindra Aerospace

    Our multi-use versatile aircraft supports many small business owners across USA. These include charter services, surveillance, freight and skydiving operations. These are unmatched in their class, are the safest, toughest and most economical aircraft, and are certified in 38 countries.
    2010

    The ‘Highest selling tractor’ accolade

    Mahindra tractors become the world’s highest selling tractors.
    2011

    A joint venture with Rabobank Group

    Our company MUSA provides dealer and retail financing options to support the sale of tractors in USA. We entered into a joint venture with De Lage Landen, a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Rabobank Group, to form Mahindra Finance, USA. This branch of ours serves as the primary financier for MUSA products.
    2013

    Tech Mahindra in the US

    Tech Mahindra, our world-class IT services company employs thousands of Americans to render companies more productive. Today, it spans across 34 locations, 15 development centers, and boasts of more than 350 USA customers. We also ventured into a project called the Mahindra North American Technical Centre. With the Americas being our fastest growing market, at $4 billion, we are also ranked fifth in India.
    2016

    GenZe

    Our electric scooter, GenZe, is a breakthrough all-American product. Conceived in Silicon Valley and manufactured in Michigan, our two-wheeler marries the thrifty Indian engineering mindset with the best of American technical talent.

    Tech Mahindra partners with Wall Street Journal

    Tech Mahindra collaborates with Wall Street Journal on a multimedia custom-content program that promises to challenge conventional thinking, drive vital conversations and illustrate the potential benefits of growing connectivity. The campaign is designed to deliver unique insights from top thought leaders on what the future means for them.

    Partnership with Scoot

    Mahindra GenZe joins hands with Scoot networks, an urban mobility solutions provider in California. This partnership exhibits the opportunities presented by the new sharing economy by offering relevant and affordable technology.
    2017

    Mahindra North America launches factory

    Rick Haas, the President and CEO of Mahindra Automotive North America, announced Detroit’s first new OEM operation in over 25 years. Looking forward, we have plans of creating over 600 jobs and investments of $800m by 2020.
    2018

    Our ROXOR venture

    Mahindra Automotive North America unveiled the Mahindra ROXOR, an off-road vehicle with modern innovation. ROXOR manufacture was important in two ways – it was Mahindra’s first vehicle to be made and launched in USA and it was the first vehicle made in a new auto plant in Detroit, in 25 years.

    Setting up the Mahindra Ag Tech Center, Virginia

    In May 2018, we set up the Mahindra Ag Tech Center in the United States at Virginia Tech Corporate Research Center. This research facility will focus on creating breakthrough technology products for the North American agriculture market and enable us to stay ahead globally.
